title: Finlay and Higuain score, Crew beats Toronto FC 2-0
text:
Ethan Finlay and Federico Higuain score, Crew beats Toronto FC 2-0 THE ASSOCIATED PRESS  19  19   
People: Photo Gallery: 
Click to view (3 Photos) 
TORONTO â€” Ethan Finlay and Federico Higuain scored to help the Columbus Crew beat Toronto FC 2-0 on Saturday. 
The Crew (14-11-8) ended Toronto's club-record winning streak at four games. Toronto dropped to 15-14-4. 
Finlay opened the scoring in the 40th minute and Federico Higuain connected in second-half stoppage time. Finlay put Gaston Sauro's header past a sprawling Joe Bendik for his 10th goal of the season.
